@wordwrap
@tab 8
   
@node sect0 "Name"
fuse-utils - various ZX Spectrum related utilities    
@endnode

@node sect1 "Description"
The Fuse (Free Unix Spectrum Emulator) utilities are a small suite of utilities relating to some of the file formats used by ZX Spectrum emulators. The currently available utilities are: @{i}audio2tape@{ui} @{lindent 3}
Convert an audio file into a tape format. @{lindent 0}


@{i}createhdf@{ui} @{lindent 3}
Create a blank IDE hard disk image in .hdf format. @{lindent 0}


@{i}listbasic@{ui} @{lindent 3}
Extract the BASIC program from a ZX Spectrum file. @{lindent 0}


@{i}profile2map@{ui} @{lindent 3}
Convert Fuse profiler output into Z80-style map format. @{lindent 0}


@{i}raw2hdf@{ui} @{lindent 3}
Create an .hdf hard disk image from a raw data file. @{lindent 0}


@{i}rzxcheck@{ui} @{lindent 3}
Verify the `competition mode' signature in an RZX input recording file. @{lindent 0}


@{i}rzxdump@{ui} @{lindent 3}
Display the contents of an RZX file. @{lindent 0}


@{i}rzxtool@{ui} @{lindent 3}
Make simple modifications to an RZX file. @{lindent 0}


@{i}scl2trd@{ui} @{lindent 3}
Convert .scl disk images into .trd format. @{lindent 0}


@{i}snap2tzx@{ui} @{lindent 3}
Convert a snapshot into a .tzx tape image. @{lindent 0}


@{i}snapconv@{ui} @{lindent 3}
Convert between various snapshot formats. @{lindent 0}


@{i}tape2wav@{ui} @{lindent 3}
Convert a tape file into .wav audio format. @{lindent 0}


@{i}tapeconv@{ui} @{lindent 3}
Convert between various tape formats. @{lindent 0}


@{i}tzxlist@{ui} @{lindent 3}
Display the contents of a .tzx tape image. @{lindent 0}
   


@endnode

